org.jetel.util.property

Class ComponentXMLAttributes

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.util.property.ComponentXMLAttributes

  • public class ComponentXMLAttributes
extends java.lang.Object
    Helper class (wrapper) around NamedNodeMap with possibility to parse string values into integers, booleans, doubles..
    Used in conjunction with org.jetel.Component.*
    MAX_INT,MIN_INT,MAX_DOUBLE, MIN_DOUBLE constants are defined and are translated to appropriate int or double values when getInteger(), getDouble() methods are called.
    Converts any child nodes of form <attr name="xyz">abcd</attr> into attribute of the current node with name="xyz" and value="abcd".
    Example:
      <Node id="mynode" name="xyz" append="yes">
        <attr name="query">
                        select * from my_table;
        </attr>
        <attr name="code">
                        a=b*10-20%50;
        </attr>
  </Node>
    There will be following attribute/value pairs available for getXXX() calls:
    • id - "mynode"
    • name - "xyz"
    • append - "yes"
    • query - "select * from my_table;"
    • code - "a=b*10-20%50;"
    Since:
    July 25, 2002

      • exists

        public boolean exists(java.lang.String key)
        Checks whether specified attribute exists (XML node has such attribute defined) and has a non-empty value (after graph parameter resolution).

        Since 4.0 returns false if the attribute exists, but its value is empty.

        Parameters:
        key - name of the attribute
        Returns:
        true if exists and is not empty, otherwise false

      • getTimeInterval

        public long getTimeInterval(java.lang.String key)
                     throws AttributeNotFoundException
        Returns the time interval duration from the specified XML attribute. Numbers without a unit are regarded as milliseconds.
        Parameters:
        key - name of the attribute
        Returns:
        The time interval value, default unit is millisecond

      • getTimeInterval

        public long getTimeInterval(java.lang.String key,
                   long defaultValue)
        Returns the time interval duration from the specified XML attribute. Numbers without a unit are regarded as milliseconds. If the attribute is not found or the conversion fails, the defaultValue is returned.
        Parameters:
        key - name of the attribute
        defaultValue - default value to be returned when attribute can't be found
        Returns:
        The time interval value, default unit is millisecond
